The main{industry}in the village is {farming.}There are about 14 farms in and around the village. They mostly have sheep. Four farms breed sheep. These farms are,{Green Bottom Farm}, {High Royd Farm},{Greenside Farm}and {Hungerhill Farm.}
Dairy farming is not very popular in Hoylandswaine. There are 2 Dairy Farms which have not very many cows. These are{Greenside Farm,}and{Hall Lane {Farm. { {Hungerhill Farm}has lots of different animals. It has 53 Hens, 2 Geese, 18 Pigs, 3 Dogs, 35 Bulls, 11 Heifers, 1 Tup, 62 Ewes and 87 lambs.
Pig farms are not as popular as Beef Farms, Dairy Farms and Sheep Farms.
